content.text: In the figure below, ABCE is a rhombus and CDE is a right-angled triangle. $\angle ABC = 56^\circ$ and $\angle AED = 97^\circ$. Find $\angle CDE$. [Diagram: A composite geometric figure is shown. It consists of a rhombus ABCE and a right-angled triangle CDE. The rhombus ABCE has all four sides (AB, BC, CE, EA) marked with single tick marks, indicating they are of equal length. Angle ABC is labeled as $56^\circ$. The triangle CDE is attached to side CE of the rhombus. Angle ECD is marked with a right-angle symbol ($90^\circ$). Angle AED, which is an exterior angle to the rhombus at vertex E, is labeled as $97^\circ$. The vertices are labeled A, B, C, D, E.]
